# WSL-first local development

This project is edited from Windows, but local development work should prefer WSL/Linux conventions.

When executing or suggesting project development commands, use WSL first for:

- dependency installation
- package manager commands
- build, test, lint, type-check, format commands
- dev server startup
- shell scripts and Unix tools
- Git workflows
- path examples in technical instructions

If WSL availability has not been verified in the current context, verify it before running development commands:

```powershell
pwsh -NoProfile -Command "wsl.exe --status"
```

After WSL is confirmed, convert project paths from Windows form to WSL form, for example:

```text
d:\Project\Galaxy-A.github.io
/mnt/d/Project/Galaxy-A.github.io
```

For reproducible commands from an uncertain working directory, prefer:

```powershell
wsl.exe bash -lc 'cd /mnt/d/Project/Galaxy-A.github.io && <command>'
```

Use native Windows tooling only when:

- the user explicitly asks for Windows-native behavior
- interacting with Windows-only tools or Cursor/user configuration under Windows paths
- WSL is unavailable and the task can safely run on Windows
- the command is clearly unsuitable for WSL